The paper deals with index codes and decoding algorithms for interlinked cycle (IC) structures in side information graphs. This topic falls under the area of information theory (cs.IT) as well as network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses necessary and sufficient conditions for the decoding algorithm to work, which involves analyzing the structure of the IC graphs. This could be classified under the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with side information graphs, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
